<inglise> Commission Directive 90/388/EEC of 28 June 1990 on competition in the markets for telecommunications services telecommunications services (90/388/EEC) </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI DIREKTIIV 90/388/EM&Uuml; konkurentsi kohta telekommunikatsiooniteenuseturgudel 28. juuni 1990 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 90 (3) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 90 l&otilde;iget 3, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) The improvement of telecommunications in the Community is an essential condition for the harmonious development of economic activities and a competitive market in the Community, from the point of view of both service providers and users. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) telekommunikatsiooni parandamine &uuml;henduses on &uuml;henduse majandustegevuse ja konkurentsiv&otilde;imelise turu harmoonilise arengu oluline eeltingimus nii teenuse pakkujate kui ka kasutajate seisukohast. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission has therefore adopted a programme, set out in its Green Paper on the development of the common market for telecommunications services and equipment and in its communication on the implementation of the Green Paper by 1992, for progressively introducing competition into the telecommunications market. </inglise>
<eesti> Seep&auml;rast on komisjon v&otilde;tnud vastu telekommunikatsiooniteenuseturul konkurentsi j&auml;rkj&auml;rgulise kehtestamise programmi, mis on esitatud telekommunikatsiooniteenuste ja -seadmete &uuml;histuru arengut k&auml;sitlevas rohelises raamatus ja teatises rohelise raamatu rakendamise kohta 1992. aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise> The programme does not concern mobile telephony and paging services, and mass communication services such as radio for television. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealune programm ei h&otilde;lma mobiilside- ega kaugotsinguteenust ega selliseid massikommunikatsiooniteenuseid nagu raadio ja televisioon. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council, in its resolution of 30 June 1988 (1), expressed broad support for the objectives of this programme, and in particular the progressive creation of an open Community market for telecommunications services. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu avaldas oma 30. juuni 1988. aasta resolutsioonis (1) laialdast toetust selle programmi eesm&auml;rkidele ja eelk&otilde;ige avatud telekommunikatsiooniteenuseturu j&auml;rkj&auml;rgulisele rajamisele &uuml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> The last decades have seen considerable technological advances in the telecommunications sector. </inglise>
<eesti> Viimastel aastak&uuml;mnetel on telekommunikatsioonisektoris toimunud m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rne tehnoloogiline areng. </eesti>
<inglise> These allow an increasingly varied range of services to be provided, notably data transmission services, and also make it technically and economically possible for competition to take place between different service providers. </inglise>
<eesti> Seet&otilde;ttu on v&otilde;imalik pakkuda &uuml;ha laialdasemat teenustevalikut, eriti andmesideteenuseid, ning tehniliselt ja majanduslikult on v&otilde;imalikuks muutunud konkurents teenuseosutajate vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) In all the Member States the provision and operation of telecommunications networks and the provision of related services are generally vested in one or more telecommunications organizations holding exclusive or special rights. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides on telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rkude loomine ja kasutamine ning nendega seotud teenuste osutamise &uuml;lesanne &uuml;ldiselt antud &uuml;hele v&otilde;i mitmele telekommunikatsiooniorganisatsioonile, kellel on ainu- v&otilde;i eri&otilde;igused. </eesti>
<inglise> Such rights are characterized by the discretionary powers which the State exercises in various degrees with regard to access to the market for telecommunications services. </inglise>
<eesti> Selliseid &otilde;igusi iseloomustab diskretsioon, mida riik seoses telekommunikatsiooniteenuseturule p&auml;&auml;semisega kasutab eri m&auml;&auml;ral; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) The organizations entrusted with the provision and operation of the telecommunications network are undertakings within the meaning of Article 90 (1) of the Treaty because they carry on an organized business activity, namely the provision of telecommunications services. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) organisatsioonid, kellele on usaldatud telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rgu loomine ja kasutamine, on ettev&otilde;tjad asutamislepingu artikli 90 l&otilde;ike 1 t&auml;henduses, sest nad tegelevad organiseeritud &auml;ritegevusega, nimelt telekommunikatsiooniteenuste osutamisega. </eesti>
<inglise> They are either public untertakings or private enterprises to which the State has granted exclusive or special rights. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellised ettev&otilde;tjad on kas avalik- v&otilde;i era&otilde;iguslikud, kellele riik on andnud ainu- v&otilde;i eri&otilde;igused; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Several Member States, while ensuring the performance of public service tasks, have already revised the system of exclusive or special rights that used to exist in the telecommunications sector in their country. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) avaliku teenistuse &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise tagamise k&auml;igus on mitu liikmesriiki l&auml;bi vaadanud oma riigi telekommunikatsioonisektori senise ainu- v&otilde;i eri&otilde;iguste s&uuml;steemi. </eesti>
<inglise> In all cases, the system of exclusive or special rights has been maintained in respect of the provision and operation of the network. </inglise>
<eesti> Ainu- v&otilde;i eri&otilde;iguste s&uuml;steem on v&otilde;rgu loomise ja kasutamise suhtes k&otilde;ikidel juhtudel s&auml;ilitatud. </eesti>
<inglise> In some Member States, it has been maintained for all telecommunications services, while in others such rights cover only certain services. </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;nes liikmesriigis on k&otilde;nealune s&uuml;steem s&auml;ilitatud k&otilde;ikide telekommunikatsiooniteenuste suhtes, samal ajal kui teistes kehtivad sellised &otilde;igused &uuml;ksnes teatavate teenuste puhul. </eesti>
<inglise> All Member States have either themselves imposed or allowed their telecommunications administrations to impose restrictions on the free provision of telecommunications services. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ik liikmesriigid on kas kehtestanud ise piirangud telekommunikatsiooniteenuste vabale osutamisele v&otilde;i on lubanud seda teha oma telekommunikatsiooniadministratsioonil; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) The granting of special or exclusive rights to one or more undertakings to operate the network derives from the discretionary power of the State. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) v&otilde;rgu k&auml;itamise eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;iguste &uuml;hele v&otilde;i mitmele ettev&otilde;tjale andmise aluseks on riigi diskretsioon. </eesti>
<inglise> The granting by a Member State of such rights inevitably restricts the provision of such services by other undertakings to or from other Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriik annab nimetatud &otilde;igused, siis kitsendab see v&auml;ltimatult teiste ettev&otilde;tjate v&otilde;imalusi osutada neid teenuseid teistesse liikmesriikidesse v&otilde;i teistest liikmesriikidest; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) In practice, restrictions on the provision of telecommunications services within the meaning of Article 59 to or from other Member States consist mainly in the prohibition on connecting leased lines by means of concentrators, multiplexers and other equipment to the switched telephone network, in imposing access charges for the connection that are out of proportion to the service provided, in prohibiting the routing of signals to or from third parties by means of leased lines or applying volume sensitive tariffs without economic justification or refusing to give service providers access to the network. </inglise>
<eesti> 6) tegelikult seisnevad piirangud telekommunikatsiooniteenuste osutamisele artikli 59 t&auml;henduses p&otilde;hiliselt keelus &uuml;hendada p&uuml;siliine kontsentraatorite, multiplekserite ja muude seadmete abil kommuteeritavasse telefoniv&otilde;rku, osutatava teenuse suhtes ebaproportsionaalsete juurdep&auml;&auml;sutasude kehtestamises, keelus suunata signaale p&uuml;siliinide abil kolmandatele isikutele v&otilde;i kolmandatelt isikutelt, mahup&otilde;histe tariifide kehtestamises ilma majandusliku p&otilde;hjenduseta v&otilde;i keeldumises v&otilde;imaldada teenuseosutajatele juurdep&auml;&auml;s v&otilde;rgule. </eesti>
<inglise> The effect of the usage restrictions and the excessive charges in relation to net cost is to hinder the provision to or from other Member States of such telecommunications services as: </inglise>
<eesti> Kasutuspiirangud ja liiga suured tasud v&otilde;rreldes netokulutustega takistavad n&auml;iteks j&auml;rgmiste telekommunikatsiooniteenuste osutamist liikmesriikide vahel: </eesti>
<inglise> - services designed to improve telecommunications functions, e.g. conversion of the protocol, code, format or speed, </inglise>
<eesti> - teenused telekommunikatsiooni t&ouml;&ouml; t&auml;iustamiseks, n&auml;iteks protokolli, koodi, vormingu v&otilde;i kiiruse konverteerimine; </eesti>
<inglise> - information services providing access to data bases, </inglise>
<eesti> - teabeteenused, mis v&otilde;imaldavad juurdep&auml;&auml;su andmebaasidele; </eesti>
<inglise> - remote data-processing services, </inglise>
<eesti> - kaugandmet&ouml;&ouml;tlusteenused; </eesti>
<inglise> - message storing and forwarding services, e.g. electronic mail, </inglise>
<eesti> - s&otilde;numi salvestamise ja edastamise teenused, nt elektronpost; </eesti>
<inglise> - transaction services, e.g. financial transactions, electronic commercial data transfer, teleshopping and telereservations, </inglise>
<eesti> - tehingutega seotud teenused, nt finantstehingud, elektrooniline &auml;riandmeedastus, kaugostmine ja telebroneerimine; </eesti>
<inglise> - teleaction services, e.g. telemetry and remote monitoring. </inglise>
<eesti> - teletoimingute teenused, nt telemeetria ja kaugseire; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Articles 55, 56 and 66 of the Treaty allow exceptions on non-economic grounds to the freedom to provide services. </inglise>
<eesti> 7) asutamislepingu artiklitega 55, 56 ja 66 on lubatud erandid teenuste osutamise vabadusest muudel kui majanduslikel kaalutlustel. </eesti>
<inglise> The restrictions permitted are those connected, even occasionally, with the exercise of official authority, and those connected with public policy, public security or public health. </inglise>
<eesti> Lubatud on piirangud, mis on kas v&otilde;i ajutiselt seotud avaliku v&otilde;imu teostamisega, v&otilde;i piirangud, mis on seotud avaliku korra, julgeoleku v&otilde;i rahva tervise kaitsega. </eesti>
<inglise> Since these are exceptions, they must be interpreted restrictively. </inglise>
<eesti> Et k&otilde;nealustel juhtudel on tegemist eranditega, tuleb neid t&otilde;lgendada piiravatena. </eesti>
<inglise> None of the telecommunications services is connected with the exercise of official authority involving the right to use undue powers compared with the ordinary law, privileges of public power or a power of coercion over the public. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;kski telekommunikatsiooniteenus ei ole seotud avaliku v&otilde;imu teostamisega, millega kaasneks &otilde;igus kasutada p&otilde;hjendamatuid volitusi v&otilde;rreldes &uuml;ldnormiga, avalikust v&otilde;imust tulenevaid eelis&otilde;igusi v&otilde;i sunni rakendamise &otilde;igust &uuml;ldsuse suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> The supply of telecommunication services cannot in itself threaten public policy and cannot affect public health. </inglise>
<eesti> Telekommunikatsiooniteenuste osutamine kui selline ei v&otilde;i ohustada avalikku korda ega m&otilde;jutada rahva tervist; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) The Court of Justice caselaw also recognizes restrictions on the freedom to provide services if they fulfil essential requirements in the general interest and are applied without discrimination and in proportion to the objective. </inglise>
<eesti> 8) ka Euroopa Kohtu pretsedendi&otilde;iguses tunnustatakse teenuste osutamise vabaduse piiranguid, kui k&otilde;nealused piirangud t&auml;idavad olulisi &uuml;ldsuse huvidele vastavaid n&otilde;udeid ja kui neid kohaldatakse kedagi diskrimineerimata ja proportsionaalselt eesm&auml;rgiga. </eesti>
<inglise> Consumer protection does not make it necessary to restrict freedom to provide telecommunications services since this objective can also be attained through free competition. </inglise>
<eesti> Tarbijakaitse ei eelda telekommunikatsiooniteenuste osutamise vabaduse piiramist, sest seda eesm&auml;rki saab saavutada ka vaba konkurentsi kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise> Nor can the protection of intellectual property be invoked in this connection. </inglise>
<eesti> Seoses sellega ei v&otilde;i viidata ka intellektuaalomandi kaitsele. </eesti>
<inglise> The only essential requirements derogating from Article 59 which could justify restrictions on the use of the public network are the maintenance of the integrity of the network, security of network operations and in justified cases, interoperability and data protection. </inglise>
<eesti> Ainsad olulised n&otilde;uded, mis kalduvad k&otilde;rvale artikli 59 s&auml;ttest ja mis v&otilde;iksid &otilde;igustada &uuml;ldkasutatava v&otilde;rgu kasutamise piiramist, on v&otilde;rgu terviklikkuse s&auml;ilitamine, v&otilde;rgu t&ouml;&ouml; turvalisus ning p&otilde;hjendatud juhtudel ka koostalitlusv&otilde;ime ja andmekaitse. </eesti>
<inglise> The restrictions imposed, however, must be adapted to the objectives pursued by these legitimate requirements. </inglise>
<eesti> Kehtestatud piirangud peavad siiski olema kohandatud eesm&auml;rkidele, mida k&otilde;nealuste &otilde;igustatud n&otilde;uetega p&uuml;&uuml;takse saavutada. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States will have to make such restrictions known to the public and notify them to the Commission to enable it to assess their proportionality. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid peavad sellised piirangud &uuml;ldsusele teatavaks tegema ning teatama neist komisjonile, et komisjonil oleks v&otilde;imalik hinnata nende proportsionaalsust; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) In this context, the security of network operations means ensuring the availability of the public network in case of emergency. </inglise>
<eesti> 9) seoses sellega t&auml;hendab v&otilde;rgu t&ouml;&ouml; turvalisus &uuml;ldkasutatava v&otilde;rgu k&auml;ttesaadavuse tagamist h&auml;daolukorras. </eesti>
<inglise> The technical integrity of the public network means ensuring its normal operation and the interconnection of public networks in the Community on the basis of common technical specifications. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;ldkasutatava v&otilde;rgu tehniline terviklikkus t&auml;hendab selle normaalse t&ouml;&ouml; tagamist ja &uuml;henduses asuvate &uuml;ldkasutatavate v&otilde;rkude vastastikust sidumist &uuml;histe tehnospetsifikaatide p&otilde;hjal. </eesti>
<inglise> The concept of interoperability of services means complying with such technical specifications introduced to increase the provision of services and the choice available to users. </inglise>
<eesti> Teenuste koostalitlusv&otilde;ime m&otilde;iste t&auml;hendab vastavust sellistele tehnospetsifikaatidele, mis on kehtestatud teenuste osutamise mahu ja kasutajatele pakutavate valikuv&otilde;imaluste hulga suurendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Data protection means measures taken to warrant the confidentiality of communications and the protection of personal data. </inglise>
<eesti> Andmekaitse t&auml;hendab teabevahetuse konfidentsiaalsuse ja isikuandmete kaitse tagamiseks v&otilde;etud meetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Apart from the essential requirements which can be included as conditions in the licensing or declaration procedures, Member States can include conditions regarding public-service requirements which constitute objective, non-discriminatory and transparent trade regulations regarding the conditions of permanence, availability and quality of the service. </inglise>
<eesti> 10) lisaks olulistele n&otilde;uetele, mida v&otilde;ib pidada litsentsimis- v&otilde;i deklareerimiskorra tingimusteks, v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid lisada avaliku teenindamise n&otilde;uetega seotud tingimusi, mis on objektiivsed, mittediskrimineerivad ja l&auml;bipaistvad kaubanduseeskirjad teenuse p&uuml;sivuse, k&auml;ttesaadavuse ja kvaliteedi kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (11) When a Member State has entrusted a telecommunications organization with the task of providing packet or circuit switched data services for the public in general and when this service may be obstructed because of competition by private providers, the Commission can allow the Member State to impose additional conditions for the provision of such a service, with respect also to geographical coverage. </inglise>
<eesti> 11) kui liikmesriik on usaldanud telekommunikatsiooniorganisatsioonile &uuml;lesande osutada &uuml;ldsusele pakettkommuteeritud v&otilde;i ahelkommuteeritud andmeteenuseid ja kui era&otilde;iguslike teenuseosutajatega konkureerimine v&otilde;ib selliste teenuste osutamist takistada, v&otilde;ib komisjon lubada asjaomasel liikmesriigil kehtestada lisatingimusi sellise teenuse osutamiseks, v&otilde;ttes arvesse ka teenuse geograafilist h&otilde;lmavust. </eesti>
<inglise> In assessing these measures, the Commission in the context of the achievement of the fundamental objectives of the Treaty referred to in Article 2 thereof, including that of strengthening the Community's economic and social cohesion as referred to in Article 130a, will also take into account the situation of those Member States in which the network for the provision of the packet or circuit switched services is not yet sufficiently developed and which could justifiy the deferment for these Member States until 1 January 1996 of the date for prohibition on the simple resale of leased line capacity. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealuste meetmete hindamisel v&otilde;tab komisjon arvesse asutamislepingu artiklis 2 nimetatud p&otilde;hieesm&auml;rkide saavutamist, sealhulgas artiklis 130a nimetatud &uuml;henduse majandusliku ja sotsiaalse &uuml;htekuuluvuse tugevdamise saavutamise puhul ka olukorda nendes liikmesriikides, kus &uuml;ldsusele pakettkommuteeritud v&otilde;i ahelkommuteeritud teenuste osutamiseks vajalik v&otilde;rk ei ole veel piisavalt arenenud ning mille t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;ib olla &otilde;igustatud p&uuml;siliinide edastusmahu lihtkorras m&uuml;&uuml;ki k&auml;sitleva keelu j&otilde;ustumiskuup&auml;eva edasil&uuml;kkamine nendes liikmesriikides 1. jaanuarini 1996; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) Article 59 of the Treaty requires the abolition of any other restriction on the freedom of nationals of Member States who are established in a Community country to provide services to persons in other Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> 12) asutamislepingu artiklis 59 n&otilde;utakse, et tuleb kaotada k&otilde;ik muud piirangud &uuml;henduse riikides asuvate liikmesriikide kodanike vabaduse suhtes osutada teenuseid teiste liikmesriikide isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise> The maintenance or introduction of any exclusive or special right which does not correspond to the abovementioned criteria is therefore a breach of Article 90 in conjunction with Article 59. </inglise>
<eesti> Seega on mis tahes eespool esitatud kriteeriumidega vastuolus olevate ainu- v&otilde;i eri&otilde;iguste s&auml;ilitamine v&otilde;i kehtestamine artikli 90 rikkumine koostoimes artikliga 59; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) Article 86 of the Treaty prohibits as incompatible with the common market any conduct by one or more undertakings that involves an abuse of a dominant position within the common market or a substantial part of it. </inglise>
<eesti> 13) asutamislepingu artikli 86 kohaselt on &uuml;histuruga kokkusobimatu ja seega keelatud &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme ettev&otilde;tja k&auml;itumine, millega kaasneb turgu valitseva seisundi kuritarvitamine &uuml;histurul v&otilde;i olulisel osal sellest. </eesti>
<inglise> Telecommunications organizations are also undertakings for the purposes of this Article because they carry out economic activities, in particular the service they provide by making telecommunications networks and services available to users. </inglise>
<eesti> Selle artikli kohaldamisel on ka telekommunikatsiooniorganisatsioonid ettev&otilde;tjad, sest nad tegelevad majandustegevusega, eelk&otilde;ige seoses teenusega, mida nad osutavad telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rkude ja -teenuste kasutajatele k&auml;ttesaadavaks muutmisega. </eesti>
<inglise> This provision of the network constitutes a separate services market as it is not interchangeable with other services. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealune v&otilde;rgu pakkumine kujutab endast eraldi teenuseturgu, sest seda ei saa asendada muude teenustega. </eesti>
<inglise> On each national market the competitive environment in which the network and the telecommunications services are provided is homogeneous enough for the Commission to be able to evaluate the power held by the organizations providing the services on these territories. </inglise>
<eesti> Konkurentsikeskkond, milles pakutakse v&otilde;rgu kasutamist ja telekommunikatsiooniteenuseid, on igal siseriiklikul turul piisavalt homogeenne, et komisjon saaks hinnata k&otilde;nealustel territooriumidel teenuseid osutavate organisatsioonide turuv&otilde;imu. </eesti>
<inglise> The territories of the Member States constitute distinct geographical markets. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikide territooriumide n&auml;ol on tegemist selgepiiriliste geograafiliste turgudega. </eesti>
<inglise> This is essentially due to the existing difference between the rules governing conditions of access and technical operation, relating to the provision of the network and of such services. </inglise>
<eesti> See johtub peamiselt sellest, et eeskirjad, millega reguleeritakse v&otilde;rgule ja sellistele teenustele juurdep&auml;&auml;su ja nende tehnilise t&ouml;&ouml; tingimusi, on erinevad. </eesti>
<inglise> Furthermore, each Member State market forms a substantial part of the common market. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaks sellele moodustab iga liikmesriigi turg olulise osa &uuml;histurust; </eesti>
<inglise> (14) In each national market the telecommunications organizations hold individually or collectively a dominant position for the creation and the exploitation of the network because they are the only ones with networks in each Member State covering the whole territory of those States and because their governments granted them the exclusive right to provide this network either alone or in conjunction with other organizations. </inglise>
<eesti> 14) igal siseriiklikul turul on telekommunikatsiooniorganisatsioonidel ainuisikuliselt v&otilde;i kollektiivselt turgu valitsev seisund v&otilde;rgu loomiseks ja kasutamiseks, sest ainult neil on igas liikmesriigis kogu asjaomase riigi territooriume katvad v&otilde;rgud ja valitsuse antud ainu&otilde;igus osutada v&otilde;rguteenust kas &uuml;ksi v&otilde;i koos teiste organisatsioonidega; </eesti>
<inglise> (15) Where a State grants special or exclusive rights to provide telecommunications services to organizations which already have a dominant position in creating and operating the network, the effect of such rights is to strengthen the dominant position by extending it to services. </inglise>
<eesti> 15) kui riik annab telekommunikatsiooniteenuste osutamise eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igused organisatsioonidele, kellel on v&otilde;rgu loomisel ja kasutamisel juba turgu valitsev seisund, siis tugevdavad sellised &otilde;igused turgu valitsevat seisundit, laiendades seda ka teenustele; </eesti>
<inglise> (16) Moreover, the special or exclusive rights granted to telecommunications organizations by the State to provide certain telecommunications services mean such organizations: </inglise>
<eesti> 16) lisaks sellele t&auml;hendavad liikmesriikide telekommunikatsiooniorganisatsioonidele teatud teenuste osutamiseks antud eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igused seda, et sellised organisatsioonid: </eesti>
